-- Ex-Deputy Moscow Mayor to Advise Orthodox Patriarch on Building
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-01-28T14:05:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-28/ex-deputy-moscow-mayor-to-advise-orthodox-patriarch-on-building.html
Vladimir Resin, a former deputy of
ousted Moscow Mayor Yury Luzhkov, was appointed a construction
adviser to the head of the Russian Orthodox Church.  In his role advising Patriarch Kirill, Resin will oversee
construction of 200 churches around the outskirts of Moscow, the
Patriach’s office said today on its  official website .  Resin, 74, was in charge of construction in the Moscow
government led by Luzhkov, who was fired by President  Dmitry Medvedev  in 2010 amid corruption allegations after 18 years at
the helm of  Europe ’s largest city.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
